  "prompt": "Will meth show in blood test after 3 days?",
  "response": "Methamphetamine, commonly known as meth, can be detected in a blood test for approximately 1 to 3 days after use. However, this detection window can vary depending on factors such as the user's metabolism, the frequency and amount of drug use, overall health, and other individual characteristics.\n\nIf you have concerns about drug testing, it is important to consult with a medical professional or a specialist in toxicology for more personalized and accurate information.",
